commit.message:
CI: Ensure code coverage reporting will work in February 2022 and beyond

See https://github.com/gap-actions/process-coverage/issues/10

Update database of factors of numbers b^k - 1

The data collection of factors of integers of the form b^k - 1 has been
extended considerably since its last update in FactInt. The update in
this commit was generated by the two calls of 'FetchBrentFactor' given
in the comment before that function.

Improve FetchBrentFactors

This function now gets two arguments: an URL of a file containing
factors and true/false for updating/not updating the local factor files.

The comment before the function explains how to update the data of
factors of numbers of form a^n - 1. Currently, there seems much activity
to extend this data collection.

In particular, these data are no longer maintained by Richard Brent
but by Jonathan Crombie.
Move from Travis CI to GitHub Actions

Only store factorization of positive ints in FACTINT_CACHE

This way, we use the cache a bit more efficiently, by not storing results for
N and -N separately.

Make entries of FACTINT_CACHE immutable

This fixes this when used in HPC-GAP. It also ensures that calling code
cannot accidentally mess up the cache, as it could before.

Refactor IntegerFactorization

Simplify the code for accessing FACTINT_SMALLINTCACHE, to make it easier
to reason about.

Also remove some unnecessary MakeReadWriteGlobal / MakeReadOnlyGlobal
invocations, and cache the result of AbsInt(N).

Remove BRENTFACTORSAVAILABLE

This simplifies the code, and means that we don't have to maintain
BRENTFACTORSAVAILABLE -- it was indeed already outdated and thus a few
recently added Brent tables were not actually being used.

Update the Brent tables

This adds several new files and also many new factors in existing files; and
also MakeImmutable calls for improved HPC-GAP compatibility.

Update WriteBrentFactorsFiles, FetchBrentFactors

- FetchBrentFactors uses curl instead of wget and new URL
- it also uses AddSet instead of Add, to ensure uniform output;
  moreover, the latest input files from the server seem to require that
- WriteBrentFactorsFiles inserts `MakeImmutable` calls into the generated code
